law.text:
Before undertaking any improvements pursuant to KRS 91A.200 to 91A.290, the city shall prepare a comprehensive report setting out:
The nature of the improvement;
The scope and the extent of the improvement, including the boundaries or other description of the area to be assessed;
The preliminary estimated cost of the improvement;
The fair basis of assessment proposed;
If financing of assessments is provided, the proposed method, including the proposed years to maturity of any bonds to be issued in connection with the improvement; and
Such other information as may further explain material aspects of the improvement, assessments, or financing.
